<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="35.[189,310,396,422]" box="[189,310,396,422]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,396,422]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,396,422]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[189,1399,443,575]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ohm" authorityYear="1965" box="[189,415,443,469]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Myrmeleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="noacki">
<emphasis box="[189,415,443,469]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Myrmeleon noacki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be characterized by a wholly dark brown vertex, without yellow markings; pronotum dark brown, laterally yellow, medially with a narrow longitudinal yellow line at proximal half wings lack pipula axillaris in males; apex of male gonocoxites 9 narrowly arcuated at anterolateral margins in ventral view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[189,248,615,641]" box="[189,248,615,641]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,248,615,641]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,248,615,641]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Note</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[188,1400,661,1006]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ohm" authorityYear="1965" box="[189,410,661,687]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Myrmeleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="noacki">
<emphasis box="[189,410,661,687]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Myrmeleon noacki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from the southeastern parts of Europe to 
<collectingCountry box="[1002,1087,661,687]" name="Turkey" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, and was recently reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[251,298,697,723]" name="Iran" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Iran</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[353,452,697,723]" name="Pakistan" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Akhtar S. &amp; Ashfaq M. &amp; Zia A. &amp; Ali S. &amp; Ali G. M. &amp; Farhatullah &amp; Zafar Y." box="[469,680,697,723]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="180 - 190" refId="ref15228" refString="Akhtar S., Ashfaq M., Zia A., Ali S., Ali G. M., Farhatullah &amp; Zafar Y. 2018. First report and redescription of five species of genus Myrmeleon (Neuroptera: Myrmeleontidae) from Pakistan. Journal of Biodiversity and Environmental Sciences 13: 180 - 190." type="journal article" year="2018">
Akhtar 
<emphasis box="[557,615,697,723]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hajiesmaeilian A. &amp; Shoushtari R. V. &amp; Mozaffarian F. &amp; Ebrahimi E." box="[694,999,697,723]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="153 - 160" refId="ref16303" refString="Hajiesmaeilian A., Shoushtari R. V., Mozaffarian F. &amp; Ebrahimi E. 2020. Tribe Myrmeleontini (Neuroptera: Planipennia: Myrmeleontidae) in Iran. Zootaxa 4751: 153 - 160. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4751.1.9" type="journal article" year="2020">
Hajiesmaeilian 
<emphasis box="[876,934,697,723]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
). The reports of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ohm" authorityYear="1965" box="[1190,1397,697,723]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Myrmelon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="noacki">
<emphasis box="[1190,1397,697,723]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Myrmelon noacki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[254,353,732,758]" name="Pakistan" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
need to be re-evaluated and compared with European specimens. Typically, this species is characterized by a narrow median longitudinal yellow marking at proximal half of pronotum and the male genitalia with gonocoxites 9 at anterolateral margins arcuated at anterolateral margins at apex in ventral view (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Ohm P." box="[392,515,838,865]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="107 - 114" refId="ref18551" refString="Ohm P. 1965. Myrmeleon noackinov. sp., eine neue Myrmeleontiden-Art von der Balkan Halbinsel (Neuroptera). Fragmenta Balcanica, Musei Macedonici Scientiarum Naturalium 5: 107 - 114." type="journal article" year="1965">Ohm 1965</bibRefCitation>
: figs 2, 6; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hajiesmaeilian A. &amp; Shoushtari R. V. &amp; Mozaffarian F. &amp; Ebrahimi E." box="[636,941,838,864]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="153 - 160" refId="ref16303" refString="Hajiesmaeilian A., Shoushtari R. V., Mozaffarian F. &amp; Ebrahimi E. 2020. Tribe Myrmeleontini (Neuroptera: Planipennia: Myrmeleontidae) in Iran. Zootaxa 4751: 153 - 160. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4751.1.9" type="journal article" year="2020">
Hajiesmaeilian 
<emphasis box="[818,876,838,864]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
: figs 10, 14). The prothoracic markings and the shape of male genitalia of this species recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[923,1022,874,900]" name="Pakistan" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
match the typical diagnosis for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Holzel" authorityYear="1972" box="[190,364,909,935]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Myrmeleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paghmanus">
<emphasis box="[190,364,909,935]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">M. paghmanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: pronotum dark brown, medially with a narrow longitudinal yellow marking, rounded at middle; male gonocoxites 9 arcuate at distal margin in ventral view (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Akhtar S. &amp; Ashfaq M. &amp; Zia A. &amp; Ali S. &amp; Ali G. M. &amp; Farhatullah &amp; Zafar Y." box="[1053,1270,944,971]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="180 - 190" refId="ref15228" refString="Akhtar S., Ashfaq M., Zia A., Ali S., Ali G. M., Farhatullah &amp; Zafar Y. 2018. First report and redescription of five species of genus Myrmeleon (Neuroptera: Myrmeleontidae) from Pakistan. Journal of Biodiversity and Environmental Sciences 13: 180 - 190." type="journal article" year="2018">
Akhtar 
<emphasis box="[1142,1203,944,970]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 5a–b; 
<bibRefCitation author="Holzel H." box="[189,334,980,1006]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="3 - 103" refId="ref16691" refString="Holzel H. 1972. Die Neuropteren Vorderasiens IV. Myrmeleonidae. Beitrage zur Naturkundlichen Forschung in Sudwestdeutschland, Beiheft 1: 3 - 103." type="journal article" year="1972">Hölzel 1972</bibRefCitation>
: figs 97, 101–102). No new specimens of this species were found in this study.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
